sql:
SELECT symbol
FROM security_info
WHERE symbol LIKE 'A%' AND exchange = 'NYSE';

SELECT *
FROM external_data
WHERE data_value < alert_threshold;

SELECT md.symbol, si.company_name, si.industry, md.date, md.open_price, md.close_price
FROM market_data md
INNER JOIN security_info si ON md.symbol = si.symbol;

SELECT AVG(close_price) AS average_close_price
FROM market_data
WHERE symbol = '0';

external_knowledge:
;
Admin users typically have higher levels of access and can view more detailed data about securities;
The ticker symbol uniquely identifies each security traded on the market;
Trading days are the days when the market is open and trading activities are recorded;
Average opening and closing prices are calculated over the period in question for each security;
Total trading volume is the sum of all traded shares for each security over the period;

- 'tech stocks' refers to companies in the 'Technology' industry;
- 'average starting value' refers to the average open price of the stock;
- 'recent past year' refers to the period from January 1, 2020, to December 31, 2020.

